#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 21, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104rwc1665702825920.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/rwc1665702825920.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/rwc1665702825920.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"rwc1665702825920\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Compiler Output\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"rwc1665702825920__compiler_output_32057\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">The Compiler Output tab displays the results of the compilation process, including warning and error messages, if they occur.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"rwc1665702825920__p_d8723e1_d8724e1_d8725e1\">Compilation is started when you click the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Compile</span> or <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Compile &amp; Test</span> command.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"rwc1665702825920__p_d8726e1_d8727e1_d8728e1\">Will it be possible to configure the Compiler Output tab? For example, the number of lines that can be displayed, or displaying warning and info messages as well as error messages?</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"rwc1665702825920__li_d4043e1_d4044e1_d4045e1\">\n<cite class=\"cite\">Configuring the Compile Output tab</cite>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"rwc1665702825920__li_d4046e1_d4047e1_d4048e1\">\n<cite class=\"cite\">Clearing the Compile Output tab</cite>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ery1665702625513.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Compilation</a><p>When Uniface development objects are compiled, the compiler checks the definition, syntax, and integrity of the object, inserts inherited ProcScript modules, resolves IncludeScript references and constant definitions, compiles the resulting code, and generates compiled runtime objects and descriptors. It can optionally generate files that show an object's ProcScript after inherited and included ProcScript has been resolved.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2531821\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2531821\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Compiler Output Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 21, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Compiler Output The Compiler Output tab displays the results of the compilation process, including warning and error messages, if they occur. Compilation is started when you click the Compile or Compile & Test command. Will it be possible to configure the Compiler Output tab? For example, the number of lines that can be displayed, or displaying warning and info messages as well as error messages? Configuring the Compile Output tab Clearing the Compile Output tab Related Links Compilation When Uniface development objects are compiled, the compiler checks the definition, syntax, and integrity of the object, inserts inherited ProcScript modules, resolves IncludeScript references and constant definitions, compiles the resulting code, and generates compiled runtime objects and descriptors. It can optionally generate files that show an object's ProcScript after inherited and included ProcScript has been resolved. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}